Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.42,0:01:56.61,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Kureha,0000,0000,0025,,Rio-senpai!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.57,0:01:59.14,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Rio,0000,0000,0025,,Good work!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:59.14,0:02:00.22,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Rio,0000,0000,0025,,Did you find it?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.94,0:02:03.00,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Kureha,0000,0000,0025,,Yeah, safely in one piece!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.66,0:02:06.01,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Kureha,0000,0000,0000,,You can find anything as long as you look hard enough!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.47,0:02:09.85,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Kureha,0000,0000,0000,,So nice and warm!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:10.93,0:02:13.00,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Kureha,0000,0000,0000,,I feel alive again.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.77,0:02:15.00,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Kureha,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.00,0:02:18.45,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Kureha,0000,0000,0000,,Rio-senpai, you were on grounds{niwa - garden. maybe yard?} duty today?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.69,0:02:21.62,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Rio,0000,0000,0000,,There was something I wanted to burn.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.67,0:02:38.11,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Rio,0000,0000,0000,,It's been half a year already since Kanata came to the bastion.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.91,0:02:41.10,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Rio,0000,0000,0000,,She's gotten pretty good.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.10,0:02:43.16,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Kureha,0000,0000,0000,,It's 'cause she has a good teacher!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.16,0:02:44.12,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Kureha,0000,0000,0000,,Ow, hot!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.22,0:02:52.72,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Old lady,0000,0000,0000,,I suppose I won't need earplugs anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.80,0:03:01.01,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Kid,0000,0000,0000,,Madame, I think it might still be better for you to stay in the city this winter. {mid - see http://dictionary.reference.com/browse/madame for reference to why this is with the 'e'; madam = in charge of household, madame = older lady term of respect, most especially for those in French-speaking areas}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.40,0:03:04.44,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Old lady,0000,0000,0000,,I'm okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.44,0:03:07.99,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Old lady,0000,0000,0000,,I won't kick the bucket that easily.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.85,0:03:15.99,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Old lady,0000,0000,0000,,I've been living on this mountain by myself for the past fifty years, after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.62,0:03:22.75,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Kureha,0000,0000,0000,,Keep going!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.75,0:03:23.86,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Kureha,0000,0000,0000,,Keep going,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.86,0:03:24.97,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Kureha,0000,0000,0000,,keep going...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.28,0:03:26.76,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Kureha,0000,0000,0000,,Stop!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.50,0:03:30.22,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Kureha,0000,0000,0000,,It's finally coming together!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.22,0:03:32.19,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Kureha,0000,0000,0000,,Noel, can you take care of the rest by yourself?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.93,0:03:34.97,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Noel,0000,0000,0000,,Sure.  Be happy to. {It was 'happiness,' but that doesn't really apply here.~Sumi}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.57,0:03:38.27,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Kureha,0000,0000,0000,,Then how about we go get some tea?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.27,0:03:38.82,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Kanata,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.14,0:03:47.51,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Kanata,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Kureha-chan.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.93,0:03:48.87,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Kureha,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.46,0:03:52.86,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Kureha,0000,0000,0000,,Where'd it go?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.32,0:03:55.60,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Kureha,0000,0000,0000,,It should be right here...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.18,0:03:59.51,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Phylicia,0000,0000,0000,,Oh my, what's the matter?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.51,0:04:02.34,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Kureha,0000,0000,0000,,The military yearbook was around here, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.34,0:04:06.29,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Kureha,0000,0000,0000,,Kanata said she wanted to read up to find out more about Princess Ilya.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.64,0:04:12.14,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Phylicia,0000,0000,0000,,Very sorry, but if it's not there then I'm not sure where it might be.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.54,0:04:14.05,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Kureha,0000,0000,0000,,Man...{if you think it's necessary}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.05,0:04:17.06,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Kureha,0000,0000,0000,,Oh!  Naomi-san might have one at her place!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.66,0:04:19.59,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Kureha,0000,0000,0000,,I'll ask her for you the next time I see her.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.59,0:04:20.30,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Kanata,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.94,0:04:36.06,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Kureha,0000,0000,0000,,Her Highness Princess Ilya was the current Archduke Arcadia's eldest daughter, you see.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.01,0:04:43.13,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Kureha,0000,0000,0000,,I feel like I've told you already, but anyway, she was a really famous tank driver!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.13,0:04:46.96,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Kanata,0000,0000,0000,,Before, Krause-san was saying how things might be different if she were still alive...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.54,0:04:53.33,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Kureha,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.  She passed away, maybe about two years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.33,0:04:54.92,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Kanata,0000,0000,0000,,In the war?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.92,0:04:56.03,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Kureha,0000,0000,0000,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.18,0:05:01.27,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Kureha,0000,0000,0000,,Her Highness was assigned to the Imperial Guard,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.27,0:05:06.27,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Kureha,0000,0000,0000,,but she also took on the duty of expanding national influence{http://jisho.org/words?jap=%E5%9B%BD%E5%A8%81%E7%99%BA%E6%8F%9A&eng=&dict=edict}, so she ended up traveling all over the place.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.27,0:05:12.88,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Kureha,0000,0000,0000,,And then, on her way to a city, she tried to save a child who was drowning in a river...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.25,0:05:19.00,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Kureha,0000,0000,0000,,But I'm actually kind of relieved.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.33,0:05:22.94,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Kureha,0000,0000,0000,,Now this is only a rumor, but... {not what she just said. what she's going to say next that we haven't heard yet}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.46,0:05:28.68,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Kanata,0000,0000,0000,,Ilya...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.64,0:05:30.77,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Yumina,0000,0000,0000,,Kanata-san!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.27,0:05:33.47,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Kanata,0000,0000,0000,,Yumina-san!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.27,0:05:35.47,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Kanata,0000,0000,0000,,And...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.86,0:05:48.99,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Kanata,0000,0000,0000,,Um... it's Kanata.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.79,0:05:51.00,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Kanata,0000,0000,0000,,Uh...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.00,0:05:56.55,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Kanata,0000,0000,0000,,Yumina-san has, uh... she's brought Yuuko-chan over...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.55,0:06:01.29,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Kanata,0000,0000,0000,,Oh!  And Yuuko-chan is Martin-san's daughter...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.07,0:06:05.55,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Kanata,0000,0000,0000,,And there's also an old lady named Jaquette-san...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.55,0:06:12.33,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Kanata,0000,0000,0000,,She lives by herself on the mountain, and early in the morning I buy vegetables and stuff from her—
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.33,0:06:16.56,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Kanata,0000,0000,0000,,Oh!  You said earlier that the pickled vegetables were good, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.16,0:06:20.64,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Kanata,0000,0000,0000,,Jaquette-san was the one who made them.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.64,0:06:26.56,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Kanata,0000,0000,0000,,So you see, supposedly no one's seen her around lately...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.42,0:06:31.57,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Kanata,0000,0000,0000,,and since her body is rather frail, people are worried.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.57,0:06:35.69,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Kanata,0000,0000,0000,,She lives pretty deep in the mountains and all...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.69,0:06:36.76,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Kanata,0000,0000,0000,,And...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.76,0:06:37.60,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Rio,0000,0000,0000,,Ugh...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.60,0:06:39.08,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Rio,0000,0000,0000,,Fine, fine!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.10,0:06:42.20,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Rio,0000,0000,0000,,I'll listen to what you have to say, just give me a second.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.29,0:06:45.22,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Kanata,0000,0000,0000,,Okay!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.80,0:06:48.83,SoRaNoWoTo-Past,Kureha,0000,0000,0000,,It's been said that,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.20,0:06:56.35,SoRaNoWoTo-Past,Kureha,0000,0000,0000,,in order to improve relations with the holy city of Rome, Princess Ilya was to be wed to the Roman emperor. {sei tou rooma to no kankei wo kaizen suru tame ni koutei ni koshiire surun jyanai ka tte iwarete}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.35,0:06:59.26,SoRaNoWoTo-Past,Kureha,0000,0000,0000,,But if she did, she would've been the third! {his third wife}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.26,0:07:01.89,SoRaNoWoTo-Past,Kureha,0000,0000,0000,,His third!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.27,0:07:04.19,SoRaNoWoTo-Past,Kureha,0000,0000,0000,,Unbelievable, isn't it?!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.40,0:07:06.68,SoRaNoWoTo-Past,Kureha,0000,0000,0000,,So really, she would've just been a hostage.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.48,0:07:12.09,SoRaNoWoTo-Past,Kureha,0000,0000,0000,,But talks of that stopped after she passed away,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.09,0:07:17.43,SoRaNoWoTo-Past,Kureha,0000,0000,0000,,and we ended up fighting them until the armistice at the beginning of this year. {maa, sore mo denka ga naku natte tachigie ni natte kekkyoku kotoshi no atama ni kyuusen ni naru made uchi to yariattetatte wake dakedo}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.31,0:07:23.57,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Rio,0000,0000,0000,,Phew, finally here.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.28,0:07:27.10,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Kanata,0000,0000,0000,,A half-built house?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.78,0:07:31.20,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Rio,0000,0000,0000,,Wasn't she supposed to be living alone?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.20,0:07:32.84,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Kanata,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, supposedly.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.75,0:07:43.74,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Kanata,0000,0000,0000,,Madame!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.74,0:07:46.72,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Madam,0000,0000,0000,,I see...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.06,0:07:49.02,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Madam,0000,0000,0000,,Yuuko told you.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.02,0:07:49.64,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Kanata,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.70,0:07:52.79,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Madam,0000,0000,0000,,She's a good girl.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.72,0:07:57.78,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Madam,0000,0000,0000,,She's too good to become that snot-nosed Martin's daughter.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.20,0:08:00.24,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Kanata,0000,0000,0000,,This is a really nice house.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.66,0:08:02.03,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Madam,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.74,0:08:06.07,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Madam,0000,0000,0000,,I actually built this house.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.07,0:08:07.53,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Kanata,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?  Wow!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.53,0:08:08.24,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Kanata,0000,0000,0000,,But wait...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.68,0:08:11.50,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Kanata,0000,0000,0000,,What about the house over there?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.85,0:08:15.11,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Madam,0000,0000,0000,,That's for my son...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.11,0:08:17.30,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Kanata,0000,0000,0000,,You have a son?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.30,0:08:21.16,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Madam,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, though he's in a faraway city right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.91,0:08:24.15,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Madam,0000,0000,0000,,I keep it ready for him for whenever he decides to come home.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.46,0:08:30.67,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Madam,0000,0000,0000,,That way it can be used easily by my son and that person, you know?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.18,0:08:34.22,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Madam,0000,0000,0000,,I need to keep it properly cleaned.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.81,0:08:50.04,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Rio,0000,0000,0000,,When will your son come home, Madame?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.64,0:08:52.30,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Madam,0000,0000,0000,,Soon, soon.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.30,0:08:55.10,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Rio,0000,0000,0000,,What's "soon" is winter.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.10,0:08:58.49,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Rio,0000,0000,0000,,It'd be a good idea to get off the mountain before the snow begins to fall.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.49,0:09:00.31,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Madam,0000,0000,0000,,I can't do that.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.30,0:09:07.93,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Madam,0000,0000,0000,,I need to finish building that house.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.93,0:09:12.43,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Madam,0000,0000,0000,,I have no intention of leaving before that, no matter what.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.43,0:09:12.85,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Kanata,0000,0000,0000,,But—
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.85,0:09:14.32,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Rio,0000,0000,0000,,Don't be stupid!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.00,0:09:17.13,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Rio,0000,0000,0000,,What about the preparations for winter?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.13,0:09:19.33,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Rio,0000,0000,0000,,Do you have firewood?  Provisions?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.33,0:09:21.30,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Rio,0000,0000,0000,,You haven't made any preparations at all, have you?!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.67,0:09:25.09,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Madam,0000,0000,0000,,It'll work out.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.09,0:09:29.35,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Madam,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you for caring, girls.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.16,0:09:31.91,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Kanata,0000,0000,0000,,Madame!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.74,0:09:41.67,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Rio,0000,0000,0000,,Sheesh, what a stubborn old lady!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.24,0:09:46.26,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Phylicia,0000,0000,0000,,It takes one to know one, I bet.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.26,0:09:47.92,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Rio,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, leave me alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.92,0:09:49.47,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Rio,0000,0000,0000,,Why would I...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.47,0:09:54.19,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Phylicia,0000,0000,0000,,Since sometimes you also, Rio, put on a front and won't listen when you know you should.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.51,0:09:55.46,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Rio,0000,0000,0000,,Shut up!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.54,0:09:59.71,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Phylicia,0000,0000,0000,,Say, about that letter...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.31,0:10:02.99,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Phylicia,0000,0000,0000,,Why did you show it to me?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.46,0:10:09.29,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Phylicia,0000,0000,0000,,It already came across in last week's scheduled communications...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.29,0:10:14.65,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Phylicia,0000,0000,0000,,The fact is, the Roman army on the Eastern border has begun to move.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.64,0:10:41.83,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Shopkeep,0000,0000,0025,,I see!  Those are for old lady Jaquette, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.83,0:10:44.28,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Shopkeep,0000,0000,0025,,Okay!  Then take these along, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.02,0:10:46.40,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Kanata,0000,0000,0025,,Thank you!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.40,0:10:47.70,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Man,0000,0000,0025,,By the way...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.00,0:10:49.63,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Narrator?,0000,0000,0025,,you wouldn't know what's going on
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.63,0:10:51.47,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Man,0000,0000,0025,,with the peace talks, would you?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.47,0:10:54.73,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Kanata,0000,0000,0000,,I'm... sorry, I don't.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.73,0:10:57.37,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Shopkeep,0000,0000,0000,,If only Princess Ilya were still alive...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.37,0:10:59.24,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Man,0000,0000,0000,,Speaking of that, Martin,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.12,0:11:03.47,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Man,0000,0000,0000,,Ilya-sama had a younger sister, didn't she?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.11,0:11:05.47,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Shopkeep,0000,0000,0000,,And 4,000,000 in change!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.47,0:11:06.75,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Man,0000,0000,0000,,That's fresh news.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.19,0:11:12.50,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Man,0000,0000,0000,,Well actually, the Archduke had her elsewhere{i.e. she's illegitimate}, so most people don't talk about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.14,0:11:16.32,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Man,0000,0000,0000,,She's something like the third-in-line for succession.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.61,0:11:19.25,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Kanata,0000,0000,0000,,Um, that little sister is...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.12,0:11:28.05,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Kanata,0000,0000,0000,,See you!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.05,0:11:29.36,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Shopkeep,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.60,0:11:31.66,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Kanata,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.12,0:11:37.65,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Rio,0000,0000,0000,,You wanna... take a little walk?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.75,0:11:40.62,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Rio,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Kanata...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.30,0:11:44.76,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Rio,0000,0000,0000,,What kind of place was the village where you were born?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.91,0:11:48.64,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Kanata,0000,0000,0000,,Just a typical countryside village.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.06,0:11:55.29,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Kanata,0000,0000,0000,,There were lots of fields, cows, and sheep, but not so many people.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.24,0:11:58.64,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Kanata,0000,0000,0000,,I guess that's the biggest difference between here and there.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.37,0:12:01.23,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Rio,0000,0000,0000,,But it was a good place, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.85,0:12:04.65,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Rio,0000,0000,0000,,And you had good parents too, didn't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.65,0:12:06.24,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Rio,0000,0000,0000,,I can tell just by looking at you.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.80,0:12:10.50,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Kanata,0000,0000,0000,,Where did you grow up, senpai?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.54,0:12:22.47,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Rio,0000,0000,0000,,In a small village a short distance from the capital, with pretty forests and lakes.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.35,0:12:27.81,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Rio,0000,0000,0000,,I lived there with my mother.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.81,0:12:32.22,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Rio,0000,0000,0000,,It was boring.  The days were too calm and nothing ever happened.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.83,0:12:40.04,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Rio,0000,0000,0000,,The only relief{comfort} was when my sister,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.92,0:12:45.77,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Rio,0000,0000,0000,,well actually my half-sister, who cared for me very much, would sometimes come over and play with me.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.77,0:12:48.38,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Rio,0000,0000,0000,,She was my idol.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.00,0:12:55.19,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Rio,0000,0000,0000,,She was beautiful and kind.  She accepted her fate with dignity.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.19,0:12:59.00,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Rio,0000,0000,0000,,I learned how to play the trumpet from her.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.00,0:13:02.61,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Rio,0000,0000,0000,,But... she was too kind.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.30,0:13:06.37,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Rio,0000,0000,0000,,And because she was, she paid with her own life.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.57,0:13:12.43,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Rio,0000,0000,0000,,When I first came here, I thought this city was like a maze.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.93,0:13:23.69,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Rio,0000,0000,0000,,I lost my way and ended up here.  I felt that, in doing so, I'd reached my goal.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.04,0:13:28.69,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Rio,0000,0000,0000,,But later on, I realized...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.61,0:13:32.94,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Rio,0000,0000,0000,,This is just a dead end.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.42,0:13:36.77,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Kanata,0000,0000,0000,,That's not true!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.54,0:13:41.87,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Kanata,0000,0000,0000,,I often lose my way.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.87,0:13:45.15,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Kanata,0000,0000,0000,,But I like getting lost!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.12,0:13:48.36,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Kanata,0000,0000,0000,,And that's just fine, isn't it?!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.36,0:13:51.47,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Kanata,0000,0000,0000,,To you lose your way... or hit a dead end!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.13,0:13:57.94,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Kanata,0000,0000,0000,,Since, after all... because of that I was able to meet you, senpai!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.48,0:14:08.27,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Rio,0000,0000,0000,,You make me jealous of you at times, Kanata.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.28,0:14:17.53,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Rio,0000,0000,0000,,If only I were able to be as honest with myself as you are...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.02,0:14:38.04,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Rio,0000,0000,0000,,This should do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.04,0:14:42.07,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Madam,0000,0000,0000,,Why are you so concerned about me?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.03,0:14:47.08,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Rio,0000,0000,0000,,You resemble my mother.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.90,0:14:52.07,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Madam,0000,0000,0000,,I know I don't have a beautiful daughter like you, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.02,0:14:56.73,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Rio,0000,0000,0000,,She had an inexcusable{unforgivable} romance, and from that I was produced.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.73,0:15:02.91,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Rio,0000,0000,0000,,She was always waiting for that one time every year when he just might come by.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.91,0:15:08.09,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Rio,0000,0000,0000,,And so... while living through such an unhappy existence, she passed away.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.98,0:15:13.60,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Madam,0000,0000,0000,,Why do you say she was unhappy?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.60,0:15:14.88,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Rio,0000,0000,0000,,Because!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.88,0:15:16.56,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Madam,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I'm{\i0} happy.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.05,0:15:21.57,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Madam,0000,0000,0000,,That man promised that he'd come back someday.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.57,0:15:26.45,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Madam,0000,0000,0000,,He promised to come for me one day.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.45,0:15:28.87,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Madam,0000,0000,0000,,That promise is enough for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.87,0:15:29.86,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Rio,0000,0000,0000,,But!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.06,0:15:34.96,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Madam,0000,0000,0000,,What else could I have done?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.96,0:15:40.39,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Madam,0000,0000,0000,,I suppose you're right.  If there was something else I could've done, perhaps I would've.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.84,0:15:42.39,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Madam,0000,0000,0000,,But well...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.97,0:15:45.18,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Rio,0000,0000,0000,,Are you really okay with that?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.18,0:15:47.07,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Rio,0000,0000,0000,,Are you really happy with just that?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.93,0:15:51.03,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Madam,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, because I loved him.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.81,0:15:57.48,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Madam,0000,0000,0000,,Because I still have my memories of him.  Because I have hope to be able to see him again one day.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.10,0:16:01.98,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Madam,0000,0000,0000,,That's enough to make me happy.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.44,0:16:16.12,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Kureha,0000,0000,0000,,I thought it was getting colder.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.03,0:16:40.00,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Madam,0000,0000,0000,,It was on a snowy day like this that I first met you, wasn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.42,0:16:55.14,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Narrator?,0000,0000,0000,,When Madame was young, Seize was a flourishing resort area.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.39,0:17:16.40,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Narrator?,0000,0000,0000,,She fell in love with the son of a merchant.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.70,0:17:26.55,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Narrator?,0000,0000,0000,,And from that, she became pregnant with his child.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.24,0:17:30.30,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Narrator?,0000,0000,0000,,But the young master already had a family.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.94,0:17:36.15,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Narrator?,0000,0000,0000,,For better or worse, his legal wife was unable to have a child,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.15,0:17:41.45,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Narrator?,0000,0000,0000,,so he took the child away and returned to his hometown.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.31,0:17:48.85,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Narrator?,0000,0000,0000,,He swore he'd come for her, one day.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.49,0:18:19.38,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Narrator?,0000,0000,0000,,Now that I'm already this old, I sometimes muse to myself...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.36,0:18:22.52,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Narrator?,0000,0000,0000,,"What if," back then...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.26,0:18:30.63,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Narrator?,0000,0000,0000,,Life is a continuous cycle of losing things, you see.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.37,0:18:33.71,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Narrator?,0000,0000,0000,,But in order to lose, you must first gain.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.34,0:18:41.34,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Narrator?,0000,0000,0000,,And the greater the joy at your gain, the greater the sorrow will be at your loss. {sono toki etta shiawase ga ookii hodo ushinatta ato no kanashimi ha ookiku naru keredo}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.86,0:18:50.72,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Kanata,0000,0000,0000,,But as long as we have the memories of those happy times,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.85,0:18:56.41,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Kanata,0000,0000,0000,,indeed, because we have those memories, people are able to go on.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.91,0:19:08.25,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Naomi,0000,0000,0000,,Oh right.  This might not be the best time, but I found the pictures of Princess Ilya you were looking for.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.25,0:19:09.09,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Phylicia,0000,0000,0000,,Naomi-san!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.85,0:19:11.97,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Rio,0000,0000,0000,,Phylicia, it's okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.71,0:19:17.63,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Naomi,0000,0000,0000,,I think it's from five years ago when the princess came by to visit Seize.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.91,0:19:23.30,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Kureha,0000,0000,0000,,Is that Shuko?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.01,0:19:36.36,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Kanata,0000,0000,0000,,Rio-senpai!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.42,0:20:39.40,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Kanata,0000,0000,0000,,To be honest, I think my parents wanted me to find a husband and take over the household for them.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.89,0:20:45.56,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Kanata,0000,0000,0000,,But I was enchanted by the sound of that trumpet...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.89,0:20:48.91,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Kanata,0000,0000,0000,,and there was no forgetting it.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.15,0:20:54.45,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Kanata,0000,0000,0000,,That person was Ilya-san, wasn't she?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.03,0:20:59.44,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Rio,0000,0000,0000,,I knew it.  You've met her as well, haven't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.39,0:21:05.47,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Kanata,0000,0000,0000,,Ilya-san's sound{oto actually from sora no oto} resonated within me, and oh, how wonderful it was!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.02,0:21:09.44,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Rio,0000,0000,0000,,And then you and I met.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.92,0:21:16.82,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Rio,0000,0000,0000,,I was probably just running away to this city.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.24,0:21:20.39,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Rio,0000,0000,0000,,So at first, nothing really mattered to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.47,0:21:24.58,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Rio,0000,0000,0000,,I thought it was just some place I'd end up leaving someday.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.48,0:21:31.60,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Rio,0000,0000,0000,,But now, I honestly believe that I don't want to part from this place.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.60,0:21:35.79,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Rio,0000,0000,0000,,And so that's why, I suppose, I must leave now.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.99,0:21:42.71,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Rio,0000,0000,0000,,Because there are things that I can do— things that {\i1}only{\i0} I can do!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:48.18,0:21:50.73,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Rio,0000,0000,0000,,I have no intention of saying goodbye.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:53.64,0:21:57.00,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Rio,0000,0000,0000,,No matter how far apart we become...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:58.71,0:22:01.00,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Kanata,0000,0000,0000,,Sounds resonate...{through the sky}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:01.00,0:22:03.81,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Rio,0000,0000,0000,,They resonate...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:03.81,0:22:08.00,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Kanata,0000,0000,0000,,And... reach out to the hearts of others.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:09.35,0:22:14.76,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Rio,0000,0000,0000,,Kanata, have I been a good senpai to you, I wonder?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:17.53,0:22:18.44,SoRaNoWoTo-Main,Kanata,0000,0000,0000,,You have.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:33.49,0:22:38.61,SoRaNoWoTo-Thoughts,Kanata,0000,0000,0000,,And thus, Rio-senpai left us.{;___;}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:40.00,0:22:49.26,SoRaNoWoTo-Thoughts,Kanata,0000,0000,0000,,Leaving in my heart a forever-resonating, oh-so-beautiful sound from the sky. {itsumademo watashi no mune no naka ni hibiki tsudukeru totemo totemo suteki na sora no oto wo nokoshite}
